arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project was scaffolded with `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -au Individual` and lives at `/tmp/sv-42180f58e22c487781a5299fea282303/ShipmentTracker/`. It has two projects:

- **ShipmentTracker** (server, at `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`)
- **ShipmentTracker.Client** (WASM client, at `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/`)

The template already has Identity auth with SQLite, Auto render mode (SSR + WebAssembly), and all the boilerplate.

## Requirements
- Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
- Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
- Worldwide users — Auto render mode for fast first load then snappy WebAssembly
- Every page has interactive controls
- Staff and customers authenticate with individual accounts (already set up via Identity)
- Role-based authorization: "Dispatcher" and "Customer" roles

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Shared Models (in Client project so both server and WASM can use them)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string RecipientEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string? CustomerUserId { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Server-side Entity and DbContext

Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs` - the EF entity:
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [Required, MaxLength(20)]
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }

    [Required, MaxLength(100)]
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string RecipientEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public string? CustomerUserId { get; set; }

    [MaxLength(500)]
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

Update `ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add `DbSet<Shipment> Shipments`.

### 3. API Endpoints

Create `ShipmentTracker/Endpoints/ShipmentEndpoints.cs` with a static class that has an extension method `MapShipmentApi(this WebApplication app)`:

- `GET /api/shipments` — Dispatchers only (role "Dispatcher"), returns all shipments. Supports optional `?status=` query filter.
- `GET /api/shipments/{id}` — Dispatchers can get any shipment; Customers can only get shipments linked to their userId.
- `GET /api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}` — Public endpoint for tracking by tracking number. Returns the shipment DTO.
- `PUT /api/shipments/{id}` — Dispatchers only, update shipment status/notes.
- `POST /api/shipments` — Dispatchers only, create a new shipment.
- `GET /api/shipments/my` — Customers only, returns shipments where CustomerUserId matches the logged-in user.

Use `RequireAuthorization` with role policies. Use `[AllowAnonymous]` for the tracking endpoint.

Register these in Program.cs by calling `app.MapShipmentApi();` before `app.Run();`.

### 4. Client-side HttpClient Service

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentService(HttpClient http)
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync(ShipmentStatus? statusFilter = null)
    {
        var url = "api/shipments";
        if (statusFilter.HasValue)
            url += $"?status={statusFilter.Value}";
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>(url) ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments/my") ?? [];

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> TrackShipmentAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentAsync(int id)
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>($"api/shipments/{id}");

    public async Task<bool> UpdateShipmentAsync(int id, ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}", shipment);
        return response.IsSuccessStatusCode;
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>();
    }
}
```

Register `HttpClient` and `ShipmentService` in **both** `Program.cs` files:

