Prompt to general-purpose agent (build-shipment-tracker):

You are building a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project was scaffolded with `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -au Individual` and lives at `/tmp/sv-42180f58e22c487781a5299fea282303/ShipmentTracker/`. It has two projects:

- **ShipmentTracker** (server, at `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`)
- **ShipmentTracker.Client** (WASM client, at `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/`)

The template already has Identity auth with SQLite, Auto render mode (SSR + WebAssembly), and all the boilerplate.

## Requirements
- Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
- Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
- Worldwide users — Auto render mode for fast first load then snappy WebAssembly
- Every page has interactive controls
- Staff and customers authenticate with individual accounts (already set up via Identity)
- Role-based authorization: "Dispatcher" and "Customer" roles

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Shared Models (in Client project so both server and WASM can use them)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
